      • matching

        @PostMapping(value="/matching")
public java.util.List<Matching> matching(@Valid @RequestBody
                                                                          @Valid java.lang.String jsonData)
        The algorithm logic is as follows: Having a list of shifts, you go through and search within the list of availability of workers, when they "match", you count the number of coincidences, this is key, because we will only take those coincidences that your counter is one, and the following add this a matching list, and remove the worker from the list of workers, as this has been paired. All this process will be repeating while the size of the matching list and the list of shifts is not the same, because when it has the same size it means that all shifts have been assigned.
